WEBVTT

01:38.240 --> 01:40.480
EPISODE 26

01:46.600 --> 01:49.000
Nai, you're a man of the world.

01:49.080 --> 01:50.920
Pick a place and get a feast out of Mei.

01:51.520 --> 01:54.000
Meeting in the conference room
in five minutes.

01:54.640 --> 01:56.280
A meeting to pick a seafood place?

01:57.640 --> 01:58.560
Pretty much.

02:06.280 --> 02:07.800
We're having a meeting?

02:10.280 --> 02:13.360
I think we should go to Turtle Scallops.

02:13.520 --> 02:15.920
The service is slow, but the food is good.

02:16.120 --> 02:18.280
Book a table, and we can eat right away.

02:18.360 --> 02:21.560
No. Their service is way too slow.

02:21.640 --> 02:23.200
We'll wait for two to three years.

02:23.280 --> 02:25.880
What about Snail Seafood?

02:26.680 --> 02:29.160
The person who pays should pick. Mei?

02:30.160 --> 02:33.280
I'm a Libra.
You know I have decidophobia.

02:33.440 --> 02:36.880
Also, treating you all is painful enough,
don't ask me to make a decision.

02:36.960 --> 02:40.040
Nai, you pick a place.
I'm okay with whatever.

02:41.000 --> 02:42.560
Let's discuss something else first.

02:47.640 --> 02:49.800
I just received notice
from Fengteng Technology.

02:50.040 --> 02:53.560
The demo has been moved up
to September 1.

02:58.680 --> 03:01.400
What's a crazy plot twist? This is one!

03:01.640 --> 03:05.600
- What about our seafood?
- Wait, why is it moved up?

03:05.680 --> 03:07.560
I thought the date was set!

03:07.640 --> 03:09.200
Why the change suddenly?

03:09.280 --> 03:11.880
Right? And by two weeks!

03:13.200 --> 03:16.400
I spoke to Mr. Wang from Fengteng.
There are two reasons.

03:16.680 --> 03:19.280
One, Mr. He,
the director of "A Chinese Ghost Story,"

03:19.360 --> 03:22.720
decided last minute, to get an operation
in the US on September 10.

03:22.800 --> 03:24.600
He'll need three months to recover.

03:25.240 --> 03:29.160
He wants to take part in the decision
for "A New Chinese Ghost Story."

03:30.160 --> 03:32.120
Ask him to set the date on September 9.

03:32.200 --> 03:33.360
What an auspicious number!

03:33.440 --> 03:35.360
Then he can fly to the US for his surgery.

03:35.960 --> 03:36.920
And the second reason?

03:38.120 --> 03:41.840
The second is President Feng,
Fengteng's top executive

03:41.920 --> 03:44.040
who's highly invested in the project,

03:44.120 --> 03:47.120
has an international conference
from September 2 to 9.

03:47.200 --> 03:48.880
He will also attend the demo.

03:49.400 --> 03:50.920
The original date

03:51.000 --> 03:53.760
is perfectly fine with his schedule,

03:54.200 --> 03:56.360
but with these two factors combined,

03:56.440 --> 03:59.600
they had to move up the demo
to September 1.

04:02.560 --> 04:05.040
At the last meeting, Nai,

04:05.360 --> 04:08.280
you said your optimization software
won't be done until September 15.

04:08.720 --> 04:11.480
Plus testing and debugging,

04:12.080 --> 04:15.120
it won't be done by September 16,
at the earliest. What now?

04:15.280 --> 04:17.120
Must we give up on optimization?

04:21.480 --> 04:23.000
It's fine to give up, I think.

04:23.760 --> 04:28.040
Since our gameplay and visuals
can already beat out everyone.

04:28.680 --> 04:30.560
It's just an issue with high RAM usage.

04:30.640 --> 04:32.000
It's not that we can't fix it.

04:32.360 --> 04:34.800
We're only short on time.

04:35.600 --> 04:38.320
True. It's not our fault
that we're short on time.

04:38.400 --> 04:39.480
We can explain to them.

04:40.680 --> 04:43.520
Decision-makers don't want explanations.
Results are everything.

04:43.960 --> 04:46.680
So, I don't plan to give up optimization.

04:46.760 --> 04:50.000
Instead, we'll take a two-pronged approach
and fix other issues,

04:50.080 --> 04:52.400
along with solving
the high RAM usage problem.

04:53.240 --> 04:54.480
Other issues?

04:56.360 --> 04:59.680
When I got the email,
realizing time is tight,

05:00.400 --> 05:01.720
I suddenly got inspiration.

05:03.040 --> 05:05.680
That's a funny way to get inspired.

05:13.400 --> 05:15.600
Automatic map generator?

05:16.360 --> 05:18.160
It's quite exciting, actually.

05:19.720 --> 05:21.120
Let's partner up.

05:21.200 --> 05:23.040
We should be done in 10 days.

05:23.800 --> 05:27.600
Ashuang, time is tight.
We have to debug while we test.

05:27.680 --> 05:30.120
You're in charge of all the testing.

05:37.160 --> 05:40.080
- Ashuang?
- Okay.

05:46.640 --> 05:47.760
Who's K.O.'s partner?

05:50.640 --> 05:52.000
K.O. is with me.

05:52.080 --> 05:53.960
You and I will finish
the optimization tool.

05:54.040 --> 05:56.760
I'll deal with the visual weight algorithm
and texture decrease.

05:56.840 --> 05:57.800
You'll optimize the models.

05:59.200 --> 06:00.040
Okay.

06:06.800 --> 06:10.320
The normal instance dungeon is over.
High-difficulty dungeon begins now.

06:10.960 --> 06:12.560
I hope you all feel okay.

06:15.800 --> 06:19.320
That means I'm the only one
still thinking about seafood?

06:19.960 --> 06:23.520
I thought the meeting was to discuss
a seafood place! You liar!

06:24.760 --> 06:28.280
Isn't that the theme, after all I said?

06:30.400 --> 06:33.360
Shanghai, celebration party!

06:39.720 --> 06:42.280
Mei, you dodged a bullet.

06:46.560 --> 06:47.600
Okay, good luck!

06:50.960 --> 06:53.160
Well? Did you decide
where to have seafood?

06:53.440 --> 06:55.880
What seafood? We got terrible news.

06:57.160 --> 07:00.000
What? Is something wrong with the game?

07:01.080 --> 07:04.280
Shanghai's Fengteng moved up the demo
by a fortnight.

07:04.880 --> 07:06.120
But that's not the point.

07:06.200 --> 07:09.880
The point is your husband,
my classmate Xiao Nai,

07:09.960 --> 07:10.960
has gone perverse.

07:12.280 --> 07:14.640
- What does that mean?
- He's become hysterical.

07:21.880 --> 07:23.800
Bring me some clothes from home,

07:23.880 --> 07:26.840
both business and casual attire.
Toiletries, too.

07:27.880 --> 07:30.560
You're going to stay at the office now?

07:30.920 --> 07:33.880
Yes, as you wished.

07:34.240 --> 07:35.880
I'll be staying at the office.

08:47.280 --> 08:48.520
Are you pretending to be a gecko?

08:49.720 --> 08:51.280
I'm bummed out, Ms. Weiwei.

08:52.280 --> 08:53.480
Why are you bummed out?

08:53.560 --> 08:55.880
Look, they won't let me play.

08:56.080 --> 08:58.000
Are they dissing my IQ?

08:58.280 --> 09:00.200
I'm a provincial champion, okay?

09:01.320 --> 09:03.360
You're overthinking it, Mr. Girly.

09:03.440 --> 09:05.320
Don't you have many things to do?

09:06.640 --> 09:08.440
My job is too easy.

09:08.520 --> 09:10.440
It's only a labor-intensive job.

09:10.520 --> 09:12.840
Anyway, working alone is boring.

09:12.920 --> 09:14.400
Two people working together is fun.

09:14.720 --> 09:17.480
You see, we can bicker
when we have differences.

09:18.120 --> 09:19.320
Most importantly,

09:19.920 --> 09:23.280
their top-of-the-food-chain look
is so annoying.

09:25.680 --> 09:28.680
How come I don't see that?
I think it's charming.

09:29.560 --> 09:30.880
You don't understand the male world.

09:33.160 --> 09:35.560
Why do I feel like
you and I are of the same world?

09:36.360 --> 09:38.120
No way in hell!

09:38.320 --> 09:40.920
Forget it. Ms. Weiwei,

09:41.360 --> 09:45.120
this is the last time
I speak to you as a human.

09:46.320 --> 09:52.520
Starting tomorrow,
I'll turn into a coding machine.

10:01.480 --> 10:02.440
Tired?

10:32.320 --> 10:34.280
Listen, time is of the essence!

10:36.280 --> 10:39.320
AUGUST 22

11:21.480 --> 11:25.560
Everyone is super busy,
yet I can't be of any help.

11:39.200 --> 11:43.920
AUGUST 23, 2015

11:53.800 --> 11:55.800
I thought we were doing The Thinker?

11:56.120 --> 11:59.560
How could you find any inspiration
looking like that?

12:00.960 --> 12:05.760
These two gods stand
in front of our library for a reason.

12:05.840 --> 12:06.960
Just watch.

12:07.960 --> 12:11.400
My soul will soon
be connected to Aristotle.

12:11.840 --> 12:15.800
Then, his wisdom will pass through me.

12:16.520 --> 12:18.640
Programming inspiration is nothing.

12:18.960 --> 12:22.280
I'll understand the meaning of humanity.

12:24.920 --> 12:28.080
How can you be so cocky,
in front of your teacher?

12:28.240 --> 12:34.040
I have always taught you to refrain
from excessive narcissism and arrogance.

12:34.120 --> 12:38.560
Narcissism can cause mistakes.
Arrogance can lead to failure.

12:38.640 --> 12:42.560
Professor Pluto... No, Professor Plato,

12:42.920 --> 12:47.440
haven't you heard of the saying
"the student outshines the teacher"?

12:47.800 --> 12:49.400
I'm not as lucky as you.

12:49.480 --> 12:51.800
I don't get to enjoy life on a beach.

12:53.280 --> 12:56.240
The student outshines the teacher?
As far as I know,

12:56.320 --> 12:58.760
you got the concept of gravity wrong.

12:58.840 --> 13:01.960
Why don't you leave
the programming predicament to me?

13:02.040 --> 13:05.480
- You, go make me a bowl of noodles.
- No way!

13:06.200 --> 13:08.600
How dare you attack your teacher?
Mind yourself!

13:11.120 --> 13:14.800
Keep fighting, you two. I've got an idea.

13:17.360 --> 13:19.080
- He's got an idea?
- Crazy!

13:19.160 --> 13:22.160
- Why don't we change poses and try again?
- Okay.

13:22.240 --> 13:23.080
Here.

13:26.920 --> 13:28.080
Time to eat.

13:28.160 --> 13:30.080
This is an indulgence.

13:31.400 --> 13:32.680
I'll have one.

13:33.760 --> 13:34.600
Here.

14:11.200 --> 14:14.120
I need to talk to you for five minutes.

14:20.720 --> 14:21.560
Go ahead.

14:23.160 --> 14:26.200
It may be summer,
but you can't make do like this.

14:26.760 --> 14:28.280
- Make do?
- Yes.

14:30.920 --> 14:33.760
Look at these people sleeping on desks.

14:33.840 --> 14:35.240
Their backs could get hurt.

14:35.320 --> 14:37.240
And those sleeping on chairs

14:37.320 --> 14:39.680
either slip down or lose their blankets.

14:39.760 --> 14:41.200
What if they catch a cold?

14:41.920 --> 14:44.400
I know, it's a desperate time.

14:44.480 --> 14:47.600
They can't afford to be stuck
in Capital City's traffic,

14:47.800 --> 14:49.920
but things can't go on like this.

14:51.040 --> 14:51.920
What do you suggest?

14:53.560 --> 14:57.000
I think maybe we could buy
some blankets and mats

14:57.080 --> 14:58.960
for the guys to rest.

14:59.440 --> 15:01.760
Sleep is important, after all.

15:04.320 --> 15:07.400
I was too inconsiderate.
You're in charge of it now.

15:08.880 --> 15:11.360
No problem. That's the least I can do.

15:12.880 --> 15:14.960
Your food delivery software is great.

15:15.520 --> 15:17.400
It saved us a lot of time and energy.

15:18.240 --> 15:19.640
That's easy.

15:20.840 --> 15:22.640
So, budget?

15:27.000 --> 15:28.360
Why are you giving me the wallet?

15:28.440 --> 15:31.160
You're in charge of it for now. Go ahead.

15:36.160 --> 15:38.360
Fantastic! We have beds to sleep on!

15:38.440 --> 15:41.040
So soft and comfy. No more sore bums.

15:41.200 --> 15:43.200
A girl makes all the difference.

15:43.280 --> 15:45.920
I can eat here, drink here,
and sleep here.

15:46.000 --> 15:49.960
And I've got my buddies.
I don't want to return to my pigsty now.

15:50.040 --> 15:53.880
Mrs. Nai, you really are a godsend.

15:56.120 --> 15:59.000
Yugong, your bed is in Lord's office.

15:59.280 --> 16:01.320
What? You've assigned beds?

16:01.880 --> 16:05.520
Of course. You, Houzi, Ashuang, and Ali,

16:05.600 --> 16:07.440
your beds are all in Lord's office.

16:07.520 --> 16:10.280
It's spacious and less crowded,
VIP treatment.

16:11.400 --> 16:13.600
Ms. Weiwei, you're the best!

16:14.120 --> 16:17.000
I believe she's separated
snorers from non-snorers.

16:17.400 --> 16:18.440
What?

16:19.360 --> 16:20.200
It's for your sake.

16:23.280 --> 16:24.240
That's discrimination!

16:27.720 --> 16:29.040
So sweet and considerate.

16:29.120 --> 16:32.000
Now, I can finally get
some undisturbed sleep.

16:33.120 --> 16:34.440
Where's my bed?

16:39.520 --> 16:40.360
Over there.

16:43.800 --> 16:45.520
You assigned Nai

16:45.600 --> 16:47.640
the worst spot?

16:50.960 --> 16:54.600
- I decided your beds by lottery.
- It's all the same.

16:55.040 --> 16:57.440
I don't sleep much.
It's best to sleep there.

16:58.760 --> 17:00.880
Thanks, Ms. Weiwei.

17:01.040 --> 17:02.120
You're welcome.

17:02.200 --> 17:04.280
There's very little I can do.

17:04.720 --> 17:05.960
School starts on September 1,

17:06.040 --> 17:08.160
so I can stay with you to the end.

17:08.240 --> 17:10.359
Come to me, if you need any help.

17:10.720 --> 17:13.200
- Sure!
- Thanks, Ms. Weiwei.

17:17.839 --> 17:20.480
I have an idea, Ms. Weiwei.

17:20.560 --> 17:22.440
Why don't you stay on, when school starts?

17:22.720 --> 17:25.760
You can work while you study,
and make some money.

17:25.839 --> 17:28.560
I don't need to get paid.
I just need food.

17:29.120 --> 17:30.320
Wire the pay to my account.

17:31.480 --> 17:33.440
You're evil, Nai.

17:35.760 --> 17:36.600
Thanks.

18:08.880 --> 18:09.960
Cousin Shaoxiang?

18:11.320 --> 18:12.160
What is it?

18:12.240 --> 18:14.040
Rumor around the office has it that

18:14.120 --> 18:16.200
the manager has suddenly
become a workaholic.

18:16.680 --> 18:18.280
I came to check it out.

18:18.360 --> 18:20.640
Turns out, it's true.

18:20.840 --> 18:22.880
What's gotten into you, Cousin Shaoxiang?

18:23.400 --> 18:24.800
What do you mean?

18:24.880 --> 18:27.640
It's perfectly normal,
for a man to strive for his career.

18:28.560 --> 18:31.840
If you truly think that,
Uncle will be overjoyed.

18:35.040 --> 18:38.600
The thing is,
I only decided to exert myself,

18:38.840 --> 18:40.560
in order to beat Xiao Nai.

18:41.120 --> 18:45.200
Yet to my suprise, the game design
was more interesting than I expected.

18:45.640 --> 18:49.080
It's a stroke of luck,
that I found my passion.

18:49.680 --> 18:53.000
Beat Xiao Nai?
What does this have to do with Xiao Nai?

18:55.440 --> 18:57.520
You go to the same school as he did.

18:57.600 --> 19:00.000
You must know his girlfriend.

19:00.280 --> 19:01.360
You mean Bei Weiwei?

19:02.080 --> 19:04.640
Bei Weiwei? I thought her surname was Lu?

19:05.240 --> 19:07.080
If it's Xiao Nai's girlfriend,

19:07.160 --> 19:09.920
then it's Bei Weiwei. Do you know her?

19:12.720 --> 19:15.720
All right, I got duped again.

19:17.280 --> 19:21.160
You know Bei Weiwei, Cousin Shaoxiang?

19:21.400 --> 19:23.680
Why did she say her surname was Lu?

19:23.760 --> 19:25.200
Did she tell you that?

19:26.480 --> 19:29.280
I know a lot of women.
She's only one of them.

19:29.360 --> 19:32.120
You know how women like to be clever.

19:32.200 --> 19:34.960
It's normal for them
to want to play games with guys.

19:36.880 --> 19:39.040
Anyway, I have to get back to work.

19:43.120 --> 19:44.600
Fengteng is so odd.

19:44.680 --> 19:48.720
Why did they move up the demo
by half a month? I'm crazy busy.

19:49.800 --> 19:53.280
Why does Cousin Shaoxiang
want to beat Xiao Nai?

19:58.400 --> 20:00.560
You mean Mr. Shaoxiang knows Bei Weiwei?

20:00.640 --> 20:03.320
- And she told him, her surname is Lu?
- Yes.

20:04.760 --> 20:07.640
She's even got to Mr. Shaoxiang now?

20:07.880 --> 20:09.680
Shameless!

20:11.280 --> 20:14.920
Did Mr. Shaoxiang break up
with his girlfriend because of her?

20:15.840 --> 20:17.040
I'm not sure.

20:18.880 --> 20:20.360
That must be the case.

20:20.760 --> 20:23.400
She lied and said her surname is Lu,

20:23.560 --> 20:25.640
likely to hide her identity,

20:25.720 --> 20:28.280
so no one will know
how many men she's roped in.

20:29.120 --> 20:33.640
She has to be a very calculating girl,
to come up with this ploy.

20:35.120 --> 20:37.280
Bei Weiwei is dating Xiao Nai,

20:37.360 --> 20:39.520
while tricking Cao Guang in the game.

20:39.600 --> 20:41.560
Now, she's hoodwinked Mr. Shaoxiang.

20:41.680 --> 20:43.680
What an unabashedly calculating girl!

20:45.200 --> 20:47.920
Didn't Cao Guang say
it's a case of mistaken identity?

20:49.240 --> 20:52.960
You bought that?
It's too much of a coincidence.

20:54.040 --> 20:57.200
Bei Weiwei must have coaxed Cao Guang
into lying to us.

20:58.520 --> 21:00.760
I'd believed Cao Guang,

21:00.840 --> 21:02.480
but now Cousin Shaoxiang...

21:03.480 --> 21:07.040
Forget it, I'm confused.
I don't want to get involved.

21:07.120 --> 21:08.520
Let them be duped.

21:09.560 --> 21:11.400
Men are all dummies.

21:11.480 --> 21:14.880
They're being played,
and they attack the good eggs.

21:15.760 --> 21:18.200
By the way, I know something else.

21:18.280 --> 21:19.120
What?

21:20.840 --> 21:25.120
A few days ago, I saw Cao Guang
with Zhao Erxi in front of the office.

21:25.800 --> 21:29.320
They were clearly fighting over something.

21:30.080 --> 21:33.200
In the end, Zhao Erxi
ran into the building crying.

21:35.160 --> 21:37.840
I noticed Zhao Erxi
has been absent-minded

21:37.920 --> 21:39.680
for the past few days.

21:41.720 --> 21:46.520
Could it be that,
Zhao Erxi likes Cao Guang,

21:46.600 --> 21:48.120
and Cao Guang likes Bei Weiwei?

21:49.800 --> 21:51.400
What a mess!

21:52.560 --> 21:54.120
I'll get to the bottom of this.

21:54.520 --> 21:56.720
Cao Guang made us keep our mouths shut,

21:56.960 --> 22:00.720
but if it comes from Zhao Erxi,
Bei Weiwei's roommate,

22:00.880 --> 22:02.320
we can't blamed, right?

22:06.400 --> 22:07.880
- Bye-bye.
- Bye-bye.

22:08.320 --> 22:09.240
See you.

22:11.240 --> 22:13.040
- We should go, too.
- Let's go.

22:29.280 --> 22:31.600
Erxi, we go to the same school,

22:31.680 --> 22:33.640
and we intern at the same company.

22:33.720 --> 22:35.160
We should get to know each other.

22:35.560 --> 22:38.240
Yiran gave me these macaroons.
You can have one.

22:39.040 --> 22:42.360
Thanks, but I'm on a diet.
I'm staying away from sweets.

22:43.360 --> 22:44.440
Erxi,

22:44.520 --> 22:47.240
I heard you and Bei Weiwei
are fighting because Cao Guang?

22:47.320 --> 22:48.680
How did you know?

22:49.920 --> 22:51.880
That's not true. Don't say that.

22:52.560 --> 22:54.920
No secret stays hidden forever.

22:55.000 --> 22:57.480
Plus, the victor always gloats.

22:58.840 --> 23:01.280
The victor gloats? What do you mean?

23:02.600 --> 23:04.480
What do you think I mean?

23:04.560 --> 23:06.880
Who else knows about this, besides you?

23:09.840 --> 23:11.440
You shouldn't be too sad.

23:11.720 --> 23:14.160
You're not the only one she's hurt.

23:14.760 --> 23:16.480
Mr. Zhen and his girlfriend

23:16.560 --> 23:17.880
were perfectly happy together,

23:18.400 --> 23:19.760
but she broke them up.

23:20.560 --> 23:23.280
Simply put,
she won't let any man out of her grasp.

23:26.800 --> 23:29.880
I had proof
that Bei Weiwei was cheating.

23:30.560 --> 23:31.800
Cao Guang can attest to it.

23:32.720 --> 23:34.440
It's too bad the evidence is gone.

23:35.120 --> 23:38.000
Cao Guang is such a dummy
that he got duped again,

23:38.080 --> 23:39.640
and said it was a misunderstanding.

23:39.800 --> 23:42.080
He forbids us from telling the truth.

23:42.320 --> 23:43.480
Xiao Nai, too.

23:43.560 --> 23:46.240
He saw the video,
but he refused to believe it.

23:46.480 --> 23:49.600
Who knows what spell
Bei Weiwei has them under?

23:50.560 --> 23:52.160
Cao Guang went to see you?

23:52.600 --> 23:54.120
You showed Xiao Nai the video?

23:58.320 --> 24:00.920
It's a terrible injustice.
We had to make it known, of course.

24:02.120 --> 24:04.400
Cao Guang came to us
on behalf of Bei Weiwei,

24:04.480 --> 24:05.720
to shut us up,

24:07.320 --> 24:10.560
but he never mentioned you.

24:13.600 --> 24:15.280
You came to me, just to tell me this?

24:17.000 --> 24:19.680
I don't want to see you
being kept in the dark,

24:19.760 --> 24:21.040
and thinking she's a friend.

24:21.840 --> 24:26.280
We might have lost the evidence,
but I think, it's best to let you know.

24:26.800 --> 24:28.800
It's getting late. I should go.

24:29.680 --> 24:33.120
Okay, Yiran and I will take you out
to eat next time.

24:41.960 --> 24:44.920
Cao Guang is such a dummy
that he got duped again,

24:45.000 --> 24:46.560
and said it was a misunderstanding.

24:46.640 --> 24:48.920
He forbids us from telling the truth.

24:49.160 --> 24:50.320
Xiao Nai, too.

24:50.400 --> 24:53.000
He saw the video,
but he refused to believe it.

24:53.080 --> 24:56.160
It's a terrible injustice.
We had to make it known, of course.

24:57.240 --> 25:03.040
I had no idea Weiwei is the target of
so many false accusations and attacks,

25:03.360 --> 25:05.680
but she's never complained.

25:05.760 --> 25:07.560
Instead, she stood up for me.

25:07.920 --> 25:11.200
If it were me,
I would've had a breakdown.

25:11.680 --> 25:16.360
Weiwei isn't at fault
for what Cao Guang did.

25:16.560 --> 25:21.160
I said I don't blame her,
but I still blame her in my emotions.

25:21.600 --> 25:24.360
Zhao Erxi, she's such a good friend
and role model.

25:24.440 --> 25:27.840
Why would you throw a fit with her?
You're so silly.

25:35.000 --> 25:36.280
MESSAGES

25:36.360 --> 25:39.160
CAO GUANG

25:39.240 --> 25:41.040
I'm really sorry, Erxi.

25:41.400 --> 25:44.480
Forgive me, for Coffee's sake.

26:01.640 --> 26:05.520
Hello? Zhao Erxi,
you finally decided to return my calls.

26:06.000 --> 26:09.800
Cao Guang, you've been apologizing to me,

26:09.880 --> 26:11.480
but have you apologized to Weiwei?

26:14.520 --> 26:16.680
I felt I was wronged.

26:17.400 --> 26:22.200
Only now did I realize,
I'm not the only one who got hurt.

26:23.400 --> 26:25.640
Weiwei got falsely accused
of being a two-timer,

26:25.720 --> 26:27.880
because the two of us.

26:28.480 --> 26:32.280
But she took my hissy fit
and your reproach without complaint.

26:33.320 --> 26:35.880
It's enough that others slander her,

26:36.840 --> 26:38.000
what's pathetic is,

26:38.240 --> 26:40.320
I always thought I was her good friend,

26:40.400 --> 26:42.840
but I never considered her feelings.

26:43.920 --> 26:47.360
Cao Guang, we both need to apologize
to Weiwei.

26:50.240 --> 26:52.360
She doesn't need my apology.

26:52.760 --> 26:55.360
And I... I'm afraid to apologize to her.

26:58.360 --> 27:00.480
You have deep feelings for Weiwei.

27:09.000 --> 27:12.680
Remember, Cao Guang,

27:14.360 --> 27:16.320
the person I have feelings for

27:16.400 --> 27:20.720
is Weiguang, who thought
I was the one he's fond of, not Cao Guang.

27:23.280 --> 27:26.160
I've never had feelings for you.
Do you understand?

27:31.880 --> 27:36.040
If we meet again on campus,
let's pretend to be strangers.

27:37.760 --> 27:40.440
I forgive you, Cao Guang.

27:43.520 --> 27:46.400
Goodbye, Weiguang.

28:04.600 --> 28:06.960
Mei, do this one over.

28:14.520 --> 28:17.640
Guys, you must be sleepy.
This will pick you up.

29:18.960 --> 29:22.360
Hello? Are you busy, Weiwei?

29:22.440 --> 29:24.800
This is Xiao Nai. Weiwei is sleeping.

29:25.040 --> 29:28.720
What? Sleeping? With you?

29:30.040 --> 29:32.640
No, I meant...

29:33.240 --> 29:36.680
We're at the office.
She got tired working and fell asleep.

29:36.760 --> 29:38.280
I'll have her call you back later.

29:38.680 --> 29:41.360
Okay, don't wake her.

29:44.040 --> 29:47.160
She'll be very happy to hear from you.

30:30.520 --> 30:32.080
Erxi called me?

30:34.920 --> 30:35.760
How did she sound?

30:37.240 --> 30:39.880
I heard there's a danger of my girlfriend
leaving my home.

30:43.960 --> 30:44.800
Bike keys.

30:46.000 --> 30:49.600
In the drawer. Help yourself.
You can take the rest of the day off.

30:51.040 --> 30:53.320
Thank you, boss!
I already ordered dinner.

30:53.400 --> 30:55.720
You won't go hungry.
Thanks for the blanket.

31:23.680 --> 31:24.680
This is a stickup!

31:27.120 --> 31:29.880
Master Er, I only have this one cake.

31:29.960 --> 31:31.800
Will you take it and let me pass?

31:34.440 --> 31:36.680
I guess so, but it's too small.

31:36.760 --> 31:38.880
I can swallow it in one bite.

31:46.840 --> 31:47.720
Is it good?

31:51.440 --> 31:52.720
It's so good!

32:06.520 --> 32:10.880
Thinking back on the past few days,
I feel so silly.

32:12.080 --> 32:16.800
Weiwei,
you know I'm full of regret now?

32:22.320 --> 32:25.760
Based on how well I know you,
you're probably regretting

32:25.840 --> 32:28.520
that you tossed the cake
from the other day?

32:32.440 --> 32:35.080
How did you guess that? Annoying!

32:36.960 --> 32:41.640
Weiwei, don't tell Xiaoling
and Sisi about this,

32:41.720 --> 32:43.480
or I'll break off with you for real.

32:44.400 --> 32:46.520
I'm embarrassed, too. Okay?

32:46.600 --> 32:48.960
- I'm not saying a word.
- That's more like it.

32:52.400 --> 32:54.120
This is a stain on my record.

32:54.960 --> 32:57.600
If the campus belle's sidekick
hadn't come to stir up bitterness,

32:57.680 --> 33:00.400
I don't know
when I'd have thought things through.

33:01.040 --> 33:02.520
But you have to forgive me.

33:02.920 --> 33:05.080
A girl like me,
with no experience in love,

33:05.160 --> 33:07.080
can easily stumble along the wrong path.

33:10.880 --> 33:15.480
- Technically, I'm the cause of your pain.
- It has nothing to do with you.

33:16.440 --> 33:20.480
It's entirely the fault
of that stupid, shallow Cao Guang.

33:28.520 --> 33:33.240
Before you got here,
I sat and thought for a long time.

33:34.160 --> 33:38.360
I think...
I must be a little jealous of you.

33:41.600 --> 33:44.200
I finally develop feelings for someone,

33:45.320 --> 33:47.400
yet he has a crush on you.

33:54.400 --> 33:58.000
It's okay, though.
I've thought it through.

33:58.600 --> 34:01.720
I don't want anyone who doesn't like me.

34:02.400 --> 34:03.920
I want to turn a new leaf,

34:04.280 --> 34:07.400
and find a handsome guy
who thinks looks are irrelevant.

34:09.960 --> 34:12.040
Looks are irrelevant?
Then why a handsome guy?

34:13.639 --> 34:15.600
Can't I have a lofty goal?

34:18.600 --> 34:20.199
I haven't interrogated you yet.

34:21.360 --> 34:24.800
Did you really move in with Lord?

34:25.280 --> 34:28.560
Has the inevitable happened?

34:29.880 --> 34:31.400
What if you lose your virginity?

34:31.480 --> 34:33.080
It'd be all my doing.

34:33.159 --> 34:34.280
He's a gentleman, okay?

34:35.560 --> 34:37.000
I don't buy it.

34:37.080 --> 34:41.760
He netted the department belle in minutes.
How gentlemanly can he be?

34:43.639 --> 34:47.159
Tell me, honestly, have you kissed?

34:48.360 --> 34:50.080
Why are you getting in my face?

34:50.159 --> 34:51.960
Tell me!

34:55.920 --> 34:59.640
We haven't, since I moved in.

34:59.720 --> 35:01.400
That means you have before.

35:02.840 --> 35:06.040
Why not since you moved in?

35:06.720 --> 35:10.200
Is he afraid
he won't be able to stop himself?

35:15.640 --> 35:17.680
Why did you take my cake?

35:17.760 --> 35:20.000
I think you can get full
on just your imagination.

35:21.240 --> 35:22.160
It's mine now!

35:35.280 --> 35:38.520
Come here. Look at you.

35:43.160 --> 35:46.320
Weiwei, while you were gone,

35:46.400 --> 35:49.000
I made a mess of Xiaoling's place.

35:49.840 --> 35:51.200
Hurry and move back in.

35:51.360 --> 35:53.400
You can't keep staying at his place.

35:55.440 --> 35:57.000
That's true. Let me talk to him.

35:58.560 --> 35:59.880
Eat your cake.

36:02.120 --> 36:04.120
No, I despise you!

36:05.040 --> 36:06.480
Based on this concept,

36:06.560 --> 36:08.280
all the player models in thick fog,

36:08.360 --> 36:11.120
whose color saturation
is lower than default setting,

36:11.200 --> 36:14.480
can all have their number of points
reduced by principal component analysis.

36:14.560 --> 36:15.880
Their movement data

36:15.960 --> 36:18.200
can be simplified and sorted
into a limited few.

36:20.360 --> 36:24.160
Finally, we can combine
player models with animated textures,

36:24.240 --> 36:25.640
and render all together.

36:25.840 --> 36:28.080
This can reduce draw calls
by thousands of cycles,

36:28.960 --> 36:32.160
thereby improving RAM usage rate
and rendering efficiency.

36:35.520 --> 36:37.680
Combining models and textures
is no problem.

36:38.720 --> 36:41.800
But principal component analysis...

36:44.560 --> 36:45.920
How's your advanced mathematics?

36:47.680 --> 36:48.560
It's self-taught.

36:49.680 --> 36:51.960
Good. You should have no problem.

36:58.960 --> 37:00.160
MESSAGES

37:00.240 --> 37:02.000
WEIWEI

37:03.080 --> 37:03.920
Let me make a call.

37:19.560 --> 37:20.480
You're moving back?

37:21.640 --> 37:24.320
Yes, I can't keep staying at your place.

37:26.080 --> 37:27.880
What do you take my place for?

37:28.160 --> 37:32.280
You think you can come and go as
you please? Move back when school starts.

37:35.520 --> 37:39.000
Who? Who's moving back
after school starts?

37:39.720 --> 37:40.680
No one you know.

37:53.360 --> 37:54.280
Well?

37:56.440 --> 37:59.040
Erxi, I just thought of something.

37:59.160 --> 38:01.360
Lord isn't staying at his apartment,

38:01.440 --> 38:04.080
but he's got many
precious paintings there.

38:04.360 --> 38:06.880
I have to keep an eye on them for him.

38:09.920 --> 38:12.480
You can move the paintings
to Xiaoling's place.

38:24.720 --> 38:27.800
What did Nana want,
by telling you all this?

38:27.880 --> 38:31.760
Who knows
what those twisted girls are up to?

38:31.880 --> 38:33.760
They mean you harm, for sure.

38:35.560 --> 38:37.760
I thought I could just ignore them,

38:37.840 --> 38:40.520
but it's so annoying
that they won't go away.

38:41.200 --> 38:42.800
They offered to take me out to eat.

38:42.880 --> 38:45.040
I'll find out what they're up to.

38:45.720 --> 38:47.680
- Take you out to eat?
- Yes.

38:53.680 --> 38:55.040
Are you serious?

38:55.760 --> 38:58.600
Yes, I got it out of her in a second.

38:59.000 --> 39:01.960
When she shows up, we'll console her.

39:02.440 --> 39:05.760
Zhao Erxi will surely tell us everything.

39:08.680 --> 39:10.480
PREPARING TO RECORD

39:10.640 --> 39:12.400
Game on, Bei Weiwei.

39:15.800 --> 39:16.640
Welcome.

39:20.320 --> 39:21.720
Over here, Erxi.

39:26.680 --> 39:29.520
Erxi, this is Yiran.
You know her, right?

39:29.600 --> 39:32.600
- Yiran, this is Erxi.
- Hello.

39:32.680 --> 39:34.560
Of course, the campus belle.

39:35.080 --> 39:36.720
We've ordered already, Erxi.

39:36.800 --> 39:38.680
What would you like to eat?

39:38.760 --> 39:41.040
- Thanks.
- Server!

39:46.320 --> 39:48.600
I'll have a crêpe,

39:49.320 --> 39:50.760
a mango pomelo sago,

39:51.880 --> 39:53.160
two mango pancakes,

39:53.760 --> 39:55.280
and a pasta, too.

40:01.440 --> 40:06.280
I... I skipped lunch.
Have I ordered too much food?

40:06.360 --> 40:09.480
No. We're all good friends.
Just be yourself.

40:10.640 --> 40:13.080
Okay, then.
I also want a blueberry cake,

40:13.160 --> 40:14.000
and a fruit salad.

40:14.520 --> 40:16.360
Oh, do you have juice? I'll have one.

40:17.520 --> 40:20.320
- Okay, that's all for now.
- Sure. Just a moment.

40:24.720 --> 40:25.760
Enjoy.

40:35.640 --> 40:36.840
Why aren't you eating?

40:36.920 --> 40:38.480
Dig in! Come on!

40:39.240 --> 40:41.120
I'm so envious of your good appetite.

40:43.080 --> 40:44.960
Turn a broken heart into motivation.

40:45.040 --> 40:46.640
You should know better than me, Yiran.

40:50.280 --> 40:54.000
You're really heartbroken?
Is it because...

40:55.840 --> 40:59.280
It's all because of that Wei... Ahem.

41:00.400 --> 41:03.240
But I'm no match for her. What can I do?

41:04.280 --> 41:07.640
An innocent girl like you
could never outscheme her.

41:07.920 --> 41:11.400
The most awful thing is that
those guys are defending her.

41:11.480 --> 41:13.000
They won't let us tell the truth.

41:14.360 --> 41:15.880
It's fine with us, though.

41:15.960 --> 41:17.560
Ours words wouldn't be credible,

41:18.640 --> 41:20.200
unlike yours.

41:20.280 --> 41:22.440
Coming from you, it's much more credible.

41:23.760 --> 41:26.840
You mean, you want me
to badmouth her to others?

41:27.760 --> 41:29.840
No. That's not what we meant.

41:30.120 --> 41:32.640
We just think it's very unfair

41:33.120 --> 41:34.440
when you see the villain gloating.

41:36.640 --> 41:38.840
Well, this requires a long strategy.

41:38.920 --> 41:40.520
Let me think as I eat.

41:47.000 --> 41:47.840
Erxi!

44:19.480 --> 44:21.920
Subtitle translation by Lu Yuhan
